e a lifesaver when logging back in to undead mobs after quitting from FD Im guessing.</P><P>Life Burn - I don't see the value of this one yet. No way I want to be at 1 HP right after I just nuked a mob for 4k. Even if there is no aggro from the spell, you can bet it will aggro because of low life. That and the fact we can't have focus items increase damage, and we can't cit on this, why risk it for 4k when I can do 5k with 2 dots easily.</P><P>I'd like VI to put some more thought into our AA's</P><P>(specifically taking out the friggen junk BS AA's like Massive Group Buff, AE undead fear, AE undead mezz, Mend companion, Spell Casting Deftness, Spell Casting Expertise, and Spell Casting Reinforcement)</P><P>And putting in more useful things like </P><P>a more efficient mana transfer similiar in ratio to Shaman's Can5,<BR> <BR>Criticals for Dots, or Dot Casting Reinforcement simliar to the Spell Casting Reinforcement skill(yes I know there are focus items for this but most focus items are not fixed length most r random effects from 0-20% and they should stack just like increased damage items add to dd crit damage)and before someone says this will unbalance gameplay, remeber dots take a minimum of 42 secs to run thier course before the full hp loss takes effect. While Wiz, Druids, Magi, nuking every 8 secs and can land crits that could easily surpass any damage we could do in 42 secs.</P><P>added HP regen, </P><P>critical group heals or solo heals just like the priest class get (now that they have made us healers :) </P><P>or perhaps massive undead criticals when a crit lands on undead, </P><P>and we of all classes should have a FEARLESS skill.</P><P>I would also like to see them change lifeburn to be more like mana burn. How is it Manaburn can be 1.5-2.0 damage x mana pool, can have damage increased by focus items, and then can crit on top of that making crits of around 18k possible all for 5 AA points, and we can do maybe 4k tops, no focus, no crit, and have 1 HP left to draw aggro when we cast, all for 9 AA points :)</P><P>Lastly, instead of having mend companion how about a new pet buff that increases resistances on pet, I can't stand it when a green mob lands a slow on a EoT pet.</P><P>Cuku - Iksar Warlock<BR>Fire & Fury - FV Server</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=223029" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=223029</a> </P><P></P><P>Edited by - Cuku on 07/15/2002  11:48:52</font></td>

