        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I only have one complaint about AA to be honest.</P><P>Lifeburn: it does not crit, and there is no modifier.</P><P>When a wizard casts mana burn....he can do 1.5-1.75x(not sure on the second number) his total mana pool.  This leads to DD nukes of 9-10k on a well equipped Wizard.  The best equipped necro in the game can do what...6k, the average necro...about 4k?  THere is not modifier to balance out the ability.</P><P>The fact lifeburn cannot crit is utterly stupid.  Wizards crit for 20k, and post SS's.  There should be some random chance of a crit, imo.  </P><P>As for the rest of the AA abilities, Mastery is amazing for 2 classes imo...wizard and Necro (Clr/shm too but they aren't a comparison really).  We use pure alteration, they use pure evocation.  This ability is much better for us than enchanters.</P><P>The junk class skills are cute, but semi useless.  Look at other classes before you get too mad.  Rogues took it in the ass.  Bards didn't get too much either.  Rangers/Paladins/SK/Wiz really got some bad ass AA, other than that, it's all kinda iffy, but we'll get more time wasting AA once PoP comes out i'm sure.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
